title: BBC Local Live: Northamptonshire on Thursday, 10 March 2016 - BBC News
summary: flood warnings remain in place across northamptonshire .
deaths and injuries on the county 's roads has fallen since speed cameras switch off , according to a new report .
more news , sport , travel and weather from 08:00 on friday .

documents.title: weather : frost overnight but sun tomorrow
text: it will be staying dry this evening and overnight , with the chance of a frost , some mist and fog patches developing towards the end of the night and a low of -1c ( 30f ) .
there will be a chilly start to the day tomorrow .
some parts of the region may be rather cloudy at times with highs of 9c ( 48f ) .
author: Alex Dolan
BBC Look East weather

documents.title: hartley says captaincy is 'on the line ' unless england win six nations
text: dylan hartley has told me his time as england captain has `` been good so far , '' but said the team have to `` just keep winning '' .

england take on wales this saturday and hartley , appointed captain for the six nations by new coach eddie jones , said he was aware they `` had n't achieved anything yet '' and that `` unless we achieve something substantial my job [ as captain ] is on the line '' .
author: Jonathan Overend
BBC Radio 5 live

documents.title: molony pleased team-mate mcdonald has been 'recognised ' with player of the month nomination
text: rod mcdonald 's defensive team-mate brendan moloney has told me it is `` great he 's been recognised '' after the 23-year-old was nominated for player of the month .
northampton town boss chris wilder , who 's been nominated for the manager of the month gong , and mcdonald will find out if they 've won league two 's february awards , at 06:00 tomorrow .
the cobblers took 16 points from 18 last month , with mcdonald scoring an overhead kick at leyton orient , which moloney said he `` could n't believe he even tried '' .
author: Joe Townsend
BBC Radio Northampton sport

documents.title: travel : a5 partially blocked at weedon bec
text: the a5 is partially blocked in weedon bec at the lower weedon turn because of emergency repairs and a collapsed manhole .
author: BBC Travel

documents.title: flood warnings in place , but `` no further significant rain '' - environment agency
text: lee edzin , from the environment agency , has said it is `` not expecting any further significant rain to exacerbate the situation '' with many places in northamptonshire still flooded following yesterday 's heavy rain .
there are still seven flood warnings in place across northamptonshire , but most of the county 's roads are returning to normal .
author: Pete Cooper
BBC Local Live

documents.title: school report : is blogging a career ?
text: children across the uk are being invited to up their pens and notepads for bbc news school report day .
it 's the tenth year pupils have been making their own reports on issues affecting them , and this time , some of the school reporters have been looking at the daily impact of social media .
our school reporters victoria , james and liam , from wrenn academy in wellingborough , look at how going online is becoming a career for bbc breakfast
author: BBC School Report

documents.title: kettering mp says traffic lights should be switched off to help traffic flow
text: mp for kettering , philip hollobone , has told the the house of commons people in the town say that `` when the traffic lights are n't working traffic flows much better '' and has asked the government to consider a pilot scheme of switching off all traffic lights to help `` cars and buses flow more freely '' .

transport minister andrew jones said he had `` major reservations '' about mr hollobone 's suggestion and said traffic lights were a `` key ingredient in traffic safety '' , but agreed to look at the idea .
author: BBC Politics

text: a disabled woman was unable to use her bedrooom or bathroom for four days after a lift broke at her northampton council house .

documents.title: couple make boxes for kettering 's special care baby unit
text: a couple from wellingborough have developed a box of items that supports parents and babies at kettering hospital .
peter and jade webb put together boxes of items such as baby blankets and toiletries to give to parents , using the hospital 's special care baby unit .
so far around a hundred 'grace boxes ' have been handed out .
author: Carroll Weston
BBC Radio Northampton

documents.title: echoes of 1998 easter floods after yesterday 's downpour
text: for many the heavy rain of yesterday brought back memories of the 1998 easter floods .
however , when the river nene burst it 's banks on good friday in april 18 years ago , the damage was devastating - with two people dying , and thousands of homes affected .

so far the flood defences , built in the aftermath of those floods , have provided parts of northamptonshire with some protection , but some areas , such as the village of yelvertoft , still felt the affect of yesterday 's deluge .
author: Pete Cooper
BBC Local Live

text: northamptonshire 's cricketers are heading for their pre-season tour in barbados , which has pleased fast bowler muhammad azharullah

documents.title: reduction in people killed or seriously injured since fixed speed cameras switched-off
text: a road safety company has produced a report analysing the effects of speed cameras in noprthamptonshire since fixed speed cameras across the county were switched off in 2011 .
road safety analysis looked at the period from april 2007 to march 2011 before the camera was switched off and from april 2011 to march 2015 after the cameras has been switched off .
one of the things it found was there has been a reduction in the number of people killed or seriously injured since the switch-off compared to the four years before .
author: Pete Cooper
BBC Local Live

documents.title: former all black captain fitzpatrick 'sees a bit of himself ' in dylan hartley
text: former new zealand captain sean fitzpatrick believes eddie jones selected the right man to captain england through the six nations in dylan hartley .
the 52-year-old likened hartley to himself , recognising the impact being made captain of new zealand in 1992 had on his own game and his outlook .
fitzpatrick said : `` i can see a bit of me in him .
i think the captaincy for me in 1992 was the best thing that ever happened to me - without question .
it made me focus on my job . ''
author: Pete Cooper
BBC Local Live
